    "category": "csaf_security_advisory",
    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for xorg-x11-server-Xwayland.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Xwayland is an X server for running X clients under Wayland.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* xorg: xmayland: Use-after-free in XPresentNotify structure creation (CVE-2025-62229)\n\n* xorg: xwayland: Use-after-free in Xkb client resource removal (CVE-2025-62230)\n\n* xorg: xmayland: Value overflow in XkbSetCompatMap() (CVE-2025-62231)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
